parameters:
Reisha: How do you find it, Princess Soara? It's nice to
spend time in the castle, but since we're out on official
business, it's also good to stretch our wings under the sun
like this!

Reisha: Look over there, wild roses are blooming. They're
beautiful, aren't they?

Reisha: Normally, they would only bloom for a short time
from midnight to early dawn, but to see them at this hour is
rare. As expected of you, Princess Soara, your luck is quite
splendid.

Reisha: The blue rose is a symbol of purity in our country.
We knights wear rose decorations to always keep that spirit
close to our hearts.

Reisha: It seems to be a species unique to this land; I
haven't seen it anywhere else. Does it look unusual to your
eyes as well, Princess?
00_st_pri_03

Reisha: (This is troubling... I thought that as a woman, she
might open up to me a little, despite our different
positions.)

Reisha: (But it turns out I'm the one doing all the talking.
Hmm, what should I do...)
00_st_pri_03

Reisha, a woman who serves this country as a knight. She
seems to be considerate in her own way, telling me about
this country, as we are close in age.

About the town, its history, nature. She speaks of various
things. She wants me, who was brought from a foreign land,
to think of this country as a good place, with such an
expression.

However, her words sounded sincere without deceit. She truly
cherishes this country, and that feeling was certainly
present in her words.

When I thought so, words inadvertently spilled from my
mouth
00_st_pri_01
Reisha. Why can you care so much for this country...?

Reisha: My reason for caring about the country? I believe
it's natural since I stand in the position of a knight...
00_st_pri_03
Is that so.

Reisha: It seems my answer does not satisfy you. Well...
reason, reason huh. Hmm, when asked like this, I realize I
might not have thought about it much before.
00_st_pri_03

Reisha: Because I was born and raised in this country...
that wouldn't be a satisfactory answer for you, would it?
Reisha: Well... if I had to say...
00_st_pri_01
If you had to say...?
Reisha: I love the wind of this country.

Reisha: When the wind from the lake caresses my cheeks on
its way to the royal capital, I feel very proud and at
peace.

Reisha: When bathed in sunlight and surrounded by the sound
of the wind brushing through the grasslands, I truly feel
it's valuable to have been born and raised in this country.

Reisha: And now, I am happy to be a part of the heart of the
many knights raised by this country, to be a part of
protecting it.

Reisha: Even when I'm far away on the battlefield, seeing
the blue rose decoration dedicated to knights reminds me of
the wind of this land.

Reisha: Along with this scenery of blue flowers swaying
faintly by the lakeside.
00_st_pri_02
I still remember what she said at that time.

But more than that, I remember how striking it was when she
let her long hair flutter in the wind and looked straight
ahead with those eyes.

There was no lie, just honesty and an integrity that seemed
to cherish the landscapes one dreams of as a child and might
lose as one grows up.
You could have laughed at it as foolishness.
But at that moment I thought, "She has something I don't."

And then, "Will I ever be able to be like her?" To love this
country, to love this wind and someday speak of it
straightforwardly to someone...

Reisha: Of course, there are many things in this country
that need to be corrected. It's impossible to blindly affirm
everything.

Reisha: But that's the same for me too. And if something is
wrong, then we just have to acknowledge it and correct it.
The country exists with its people. It should be so for many
people. For as many people as possible.

Reisha: Hahaha... what a pretentious way of speaking I've
taken up. It's embarrassing.

Reisha: But if I were to put my feelings into words, that's
what they would be. I don't know if I've answered your
question, Princess Soara, but is this alright?
00_st_pri_02

Yes, that's enough. It was wrong of me to speak as if
testing you.

Reisha: Not at all! Feel free to speak up about anything
that concerns you. If it's within my power to answer, I will
answer anything!
00_st_pri_02
Is that so? Then Reisha.
Reisha: Yes? What is it, Princess Soara?
00_st_pri_02
Do you currently have someone you're in love with?

Reisha: Ha, haa!? In love with someone...!? Why would you
ask such a thing all of a sudden...!?
00_st_pri_02

Oh, but wasn't it you who said that it's fine to speak up
about anything that's on your mind?
Reisha: That is true, but...
00_st_pri_02
I've heard that courtly romance is the flower of knighthood.

When I was younger, I used to dream about such tales as if
they were fairy stories, but now that I live in the castle
too, I wonder if such romances truly exist and thought I
might inquire about it.

I am also of an age where it's appropriate to take an
interest in such matters, don't you think?

Reisha: Even so, while the senior knights might have such
experiences, I still need more training and thus am far from
such matters...

Reisha: No, even during my time as a court student, I didn't
have such experiences either. Somehow, dedicating myself to
training just suited my nature...

Reisha: If anything, the extent of my experience is just
offering a bit of comfort to the soldiers under my command
who are feeling down in unfamiliar battlefields... No, this
isn't really the kind of story to tell...
00_st_pri_04
Haha, I'm just joking.

Reisha: What!! Cough, cough! Really now! Princess Soara!
That's not very kind of you!
00_st_pri_04

To think I could have just brushed off such a conversation
lightly, but seeing you take it so seriously was amusing, so
I couldn't help but tease you a bit.
Ufufu, you are an interesting person, Reisha.
Reisha: Interesting, you say!? Ha, hahaha!!

Reisha: I haven't been told that very often, but if it
pleases you, I'm always available to keep you entertained!
00_st_pri_04
Is that so?
00_st_pri_04

Then maybe today I'll spend a little more time out in this
wind.
Reisha: Yes! Let's do that...!
